Sure! To write an if/then statement in C programming language, you can use the if-else statement to execute different blocks of code based on a given condition.

Here’s an example of an if/then statement in C:

if (condition) {
  // code to execute if the condition is true
} else {
  // code to execute if the condition is false
}

To be more specific, here are the steps to write an if/then statement in C:

1. Define the condition that you want to test.
2. Use the if-else statement to specify the code to execute based on the condition.
3. Use curly braces to enclose the code blocks for each branch of the if-else statement.

